[1] Guangxi
Date: 5 Jun 2017
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news_detail?action=ql&uid=MjI0OA&pd=YXRsbXBw&newsId=19467


During the period between 26 May to 1 Jun 2017, the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region reported one human H7N9 AIV fatal case (49-year-old male) in Baise city.

The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has reported total of 26 human H7N9 AIV cases (including 13 fatal, 13 discharged from hospital) since 2017.

